## PHI Decomposition

### Phase 1: Diagnosis (σ AIR)
```
σ(question|concept-test)
├── target: conceptual-understanding
├── diagnose: misconception-pattern
├── distinguish: algorithmic-skill vs. true-comprehension
└── output: response-distribution
```

### Phase 2: Social Reconstruction (ρ WATER)
```
ρ(peer-discussion|knowledge-reconstruction)
├── input: individual-confusion
├── process: dialogic-negotiation
├── mechanism: explanation-effect
├── flow: between-peers
└── output: provisional-consensus
```

### Phase 3: Generative Clarity (β WOOD)
```
β(explanation|generative-clarity)
├── trigger: need-to-convince-peer
├── process: articulation-of-reasoning
├── outcome: elaborated-understanding
├── growth: knowledge-branching
└── feedback: immediate-from-peer
```

### Phase 4: Convergence (μ METAL)
```
μ(consensus|convergence)
├── structure: voting-mechanism
├── discipline: commit-to-answer
├── feedback: histogram-revelation
├── boundary: right-vs-wrong
└── outcome: clarity-about-understanding
```

### Phase 5: Transformation (λ FIRE)
```
λ(commitment|conceptual-change)
├── direction: toward-correct-understanding
├── energy: instructor-facilitation
├── transformation: misconception→insight
├── purpose: deep-learning
└── outcome: consolidated-knowledge
```

